    "text": "Skip to content\nAdmin\nDashboard\nCategories\nTags\nSEO\nSettings\nPassword\nUsers\nDatabase\nLog out\nSettings\nSave\nImage Processing\nConfigure image quality, output sizes, and processing concurrency.\nWebP Quality\n\n1-100. Higher = better quality, larger files.\n\nAVIF Quality\n\n1-100. Higher = better quality, larger files.\n\nJPEG Quality\n\n1-100. Higher = better quality, larger files.\n\nOutput Sizes\n\nComma-separated pixel widths (e.g. 640,1536,2048,4096). The 2048 size is used as the base.\n\nProcessing Concurrency\n\n1-16. Number of images processed simultaneously. Higher uses more CPU/memory.\n\nGallery Display\nConfigure the masonry grid layout for the public gallery.\nDesktop Columns\nTablet Columns\nMobile Columns\n\nNumber of columns at each breakpoint. Leave empty for defaults (4/3/2).\n\nPrivacy\nControl what metadata is stored with uploaded images.\nStrip GPS on Upload\n\nRemove GPS coordinates from EXIF data when images are uploaded. Existing images are not affected.\n\nUpload Limits\nConfigure file size and batch limits for uploads.\nMax File Size (MB)\n\nMaximum size per uploaded file in megabytes.\n\nMax Files per Batch\n\nMaximum number of files in a single upload batch.\n\nStorage Backend\nConfigure where image files are stored. Changing backends does not migrate existing files.\nStorage Backend\n\nSelect where processed images are stored. 'Local' uses the filesystem. 'MinIO' and 'S3' require additional configuration.",
